attribution.changeMessage: surname was Nielsdatter, see attached birth record.  Denmark Baptisms 1618-1923 shows name as Dorthe Nielsdr.
Matches original death record in Birkerod

Original parish record of Værløse.  The correct Niels Andersen lived at the Kollekolla farm,  another Niels Andersen lived at the Brynn farm,  these two have been confused for the same person, but they were having children in the same years in the same parish, they can not be the same person.  I have eliminated all of the children born in the Borshoj parish and on Brynn farm in Vaerlose,  leaving only those born on the Kollekolle farm.
If she was buried on 14 Nov 1784, she died in Nov 1784.  Common sense.
Søllerød parish is in Copenhagen, not Fredriksborg - see attached record
Sollerud parish is located in Copenhagen Denmark, not Fredriksborg - see attached record
His surname was Andersen, per original records of Værlose, Copenhagen, Denmark
